Description Henkel Benzoxazine 99110 is a one component liquid molding resin
which can be stored for up to 6-months at room temperature
(77°F/25
° C). Henkel Benzoxazine 99110 is intended for use in Liquid
Resin Infusion (LRI) applications and has high temperature
performance with low flammability characteristics. It is
particularly suitable for the manufacture of large parts due to
the broad process window, low exotherm, and low resin shrinkage on
cure. The resin is intended for use with the tailored binder
Henkel Benzoxazine 99900. This is a powder binder which should be
applied to each ply for maximum effect. The level of binder used
will depend on the preform and composite mechanical performance
requirements.
Features and Benefits
@BULLET Room temperature stability-no refrigerated storage or
shipping is required, can be air shipped
@BULLET One-part system-no mixing is required
@BULLET Broad processing window-suitable for large parts and
intricate shapes
@BULLET Viscosity stability-long injection window for large parts
@BULLET Low heat release during cure-allows manufacture of large
parts, lowers residual stresses
@BULLET Low cure shrinkage-improved translation of strength in final
part
@BULLET Fire retardant-suitable for aircraft fuselage and interior
applications
@BULLET High hot/wet property retention-higher service temperature
to enable a wide range of aircraft applications
@BULLET Improved UV resistance-no discoloration compared to epoxies
@BULLET Good thermal resistance-acceptable for high temperature
areas
